## pg_cron — Schedule Recurring Jobs

**When you need it**: Send daily email digests, clean up old data, sync records, trigger Edge Functions on a schedule.

> Supabase Dashboard shortcut: Integrations → Cron → New Job

### Enable
```sql
-- Already enabled on all Supabase projects
-- If not: Database → Extensions → pg_cron → toggle ON
```

### Schedule a SQL job
```sql
-- Run every day at 3am UTC
SELECT cron.schedule(
  'cleanup-old-sessions',         -- job name (unique)
  '0 3 * * *',                    -- cron expression (min hour day month weekday)
  $$DELETE FROM sessions WHERE created_at < NOW() - INTERVAL '30 days'$$
);

-- Common schedules:
-- '* * * * *'      every minute
-- '*/5 * * * *'    every 5 minutes
-- '0 * * * *'      every hour
-- '0 9 * * 1'      every Monday at 9am UTC
-- '0 0 1 * *'      first day of every month at midnight
```

### Trigger an Edge Function on a schedule (requires pg_net)
```sql
SELECT cron.schedule(
  'process-notifications',
  '*/5 * * * *',   -- every 5 minutes
  $$
  SELECT net.http_post(
    url := 'https://[PROJECT_REF].functions.supabase.co/process-notifications',
    headers := jsonb_build_object(
      'Content-Type', 'application/json',
      'Authorization', 'Bearer ' || current_setting('app.service_role_key')
    ),
    body := jsonb_build_object('time', NOW()::TEXT)
  )
  $$
);
```

### Manage jobs
```sql
-- List all jobs
SELECT * FROM cron.job;

-- View job run history (last 5 days)
SELECT * FROM cron.job_run_details
WHERE end_time > NOW() - INTERVAL '5 days'
ORDER BY end_time DESC;

-- Delete a job
SELECT cron.unschedule('cleanup-old-sessions');
```

### Debugging failures
```sql
-- Check for failed runs
SELECT job_id, status, return_message, start_time, end_time
FROM cron.job_run_details
WHERE status = 'failed'
ORDER BY end_time DESC
LIMIT 20;
```

### Limits
- Max 8 jobs running concurrently
- Each job should run in under 10 minutes
- Cannot run faster than every 1 second

