## pg_net — Async HTTP Requests from Postgres

**When you need it**: Trigger webhooks from database triggers, call Edge Functions from SQL, notify external services on data changes.

### Enable
```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS pg_net WITH SCHEMA extensions;
```

### POST request from a trigger
```sql
-- Create a function that calls an external webhook on INSERT
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION notify_webhook()
RETURNS TRIGGER LANGUAGE plpgsql AS $$
BEGIN
  PERFORM net.http_post(
    url := 'https://your-webhook-endpoint.com/events',
    headers := '{"Content-Type": "application/json"}'::JSONB,
    body := jsonb_build_object(
      'event', TG_OP,
      'table', TG_TABLE_NAME,
      'record', row_to_json(NEW)
    )
  );
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

CREATE TRIGGER on_order_created
  AFTER INSERT ON orders
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION notify_webhook();
```

### GET request
```sql
SELECT net.http_get(url := 'https://api.example.com/endpoint') AS request_id;
```

### Important limits
- Only POST with JSON body — no other formats
- Response data stored for 6 hours only
- Requests start only AFTER the transaction commits
- Max ~200 requests/second

