## HypoPG — Test Indexes Without Creating Them

**When you need it**: Safely test if a proposed index would actually improve a query before adding it to production.

### Enable
```sql
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS hypopg WITH SCHEMA extensions;
```

### Test a hypothetical index
```sql
-- 1. Create a hypothetical (fake) index
SELECT hypopg_create_index('CREATE INDEX ON orders(user_id, status)');

-- 2. Run EXPLAIN to see if query planner would use it
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM orders WHERE user_id = '123' AND status = 'pending';

-- 3. Clean up
SELECT hypopg_reset();
```

